Its clear that `suite-sparse` is not providing the full path name for `libumfpack.5.dylib` and co., so I believe its a candidate for [`fix_darwin_install_name`](https://github.com/spack/spack/blob/7a6268593ce957a54bbe8fbcb7b3e1ea1b71ee2c/lib/spack/llnl/util/filesystem.py#L1035-L1036) to be added to the package file. My question is more aimed towards some of the other dependencies, namely `trilinos`, `open-cascade` and `muparser` that only add an `@rpath`. Should these also be setting the full path name in their libraries? If I understand correctly, the only way to run an executable linked against these libraries would be to load their environment before use, which means that one would run into issues if for example just using filesystem views. One of [our users recently had a problem](https://groups.google.com/d/msg/dealii/QH92Jir2fY4/MmRvTez4CQAJ) that I think was caused by this. If `trilinos`, `open-cascade` and `muparser` are also candidates to use `fix_darwin_install_name` then I'll add them to #19507.

Thanks a lot for your time!
